## Requests from the screen reader

The Orca screen reader can explicitly request for information for a given widget of a given application, for instance getText:

* Orca calls pyatspi getText method on a pyatspi object corresponding to the widget
* pyatspi's getText method (implemented in text.py) calls Atspi.Text.get_text, which is a python binding for the C atspi_text_get_text function from libatspi.so provided by at-spi2-core
* atspi_text_get_text creates an RPC message for the dbus sender of the application and the path for the widget, using the org.a11y.atspi.Text dbus interface, the GetText method.

